# API Layer

## BFF integrations via generated API clients (Kubb)
- The BFF calls multiple upstream APIs 
- Generated artifacts are written under `src/shared/apis/<api>/`.
- Do not edit generated files by hand; re-run generation via Kubb when the schema changes.


## Generated folder layout (per API)
Each API directory under `src/shared/apis/<api>/` contains:
- `clients/`: Generated functions for each endpoint.
- `mocks/`: Functions that create mocks of the API models for unit tests.
- `models/`: TypeScript types for each API model, used by DTOs to map from API shapes to internal DTOs.

## How services use generated clients
- Services import from `@/shared/apis/<api>/clients` to call endpoints.
- Services map `@/shared/apis/<api>/models` to internal DTOs in `@/shared/dtos`.
- Unit tests use `@/shared/apis/<api>/mocks` for fast, deterministic fixtures.

## tRPC contract and type imports
- tRPC procedures call services (not generated clients) and expose typed inputs/outputs.
- Frontend code should import types from the generated tRPC types (`RouterOutputs`, `RouterInputs`, `AppRouter`).
- Never create local type definitions for API models; rely on DTOs on the server and tRPC types at the boundary.
